{##
 # MCP AI Integration — Admin Settings Page
 #
 # @ListChild (list="admin.center", zone="admin")
 #}

{% extends 'admin/settings/body.twig' %}

{% block settings_body %}
{% set webDir = config.Security.web_dir|default('') %}
{% set ollamaEnabled = config.XC.MCP.ollama_enabled|default(false) %}
{% set ollamaModel = config.XC.MCP.ollama_model|default('gemma4:e4b') %}

<div class="mcp-settings">

  <div class="mcp-tabs" role="tablist">
    <button type="button" class="mcp-tab active" data-tab="connection" role="tab" aria-selected="true">{{ t('Connection') }}</button>
    <button type="button" class="mcp-tab" data-tab="chat" role="tab" aria-selected="false">{{ t('Chat') }}</button>
  </div>

  {# ─────────────────────────── Tab 1: Connection ─────────────────────────── #}
  <div class="mcp-tab-panel active" data-panel="connection" role="tabpanel">

    <div class="settings-section">
      <h2>{{ t('Connection') }}</h2>

      <table class="settings-table connection-info-table">
        <tr>
          <td class="setting-name">
            <label>{{ t('HTTP Endpoint') }}</label>
            <p class="help-text">{{ t('Use this URL in your MCP client configuration.') }}</p>
          </td>
          <td class="setting-value">
            <input type="text" value="{{ webDir }}/mcp" class="form-control connection-url" readonly size="60" onclick="this.select()" />
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="setting-name">
            <label>{{ t('API Key') }}</label>
            <p class="help-text">{{ t('Current static API key. Generated on install.') }}</p>
          </td>
          <td class="setting-value">
            {% set currentKey = config.XC.MCP.mcp_api_key|default('') %}
            {% if currentKey %}
              <code class="api-key-display" onclick="this.classList.toggle('revealed')">{{ currentKey }}</code>
            {% else %}
              <span class="text-muted">{{ t('Not set — using X-Cart API keys from database') }}</span>
            {% endif %}
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="setting-name">
            <label>{{ t('Claude Desktop / Cursor Config') }}</label>
            <p class="help-text">{{ t('Copy this JSON to your MCP client config file.') }}</p>
          </td>
          <td class="setting-value">
            <textarea class="form-control config-json" readonly rows="8" cols="60" onclick="this.select()">{
  "mcpServers": {
    "xcart": {
      "url": "{{ webDir|default('https://your-store.com') }}/mcp",
      "headers": {
        "Authorization": "Bearer {{ config.XC.MCP.mcp_api_key|default('YOUR_API_KEY') }}"
      }
    }
  }
}</textarea>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="setting-name">
            <label>{{ t('AI Agent Setup Prompt') }}</label>
            <p class="help-text">{{ t('Click "Copy as prompt", paste it into your AI assistant (Claude, Cursor, etc.) and it will connect this MCP server for you.') }}</p>
            <button type="button" class="btn regular-button" onclick="mcpCopyPrompt(this)">{{ t('Copy as prompt') }}</button>
          </td>
          <td class="setting-value">
            {% set mcpKey = config.XC.MCP.mcp_api_key|default('YOUR_API_KEY') %}
            <textarea id="mcp-agent-prompt" class="form-control agent-prompt" readonly rows="14" cols="60" onclick="this.select()">Please connect my AI client to an X-Cart store over the Model Context Protocol (MCP).

Server:
- Transport: Streamable HTTP
- Endpoint URL: __MCP_ENDPOINT__
- Authentication: HTTP header  Authorization: Bearer {{ mcpKey }}

Do the following:
1. If my client supports remote / streamable-HTTP MCP servers (Cursor, Codex, VS Code, custom clients), add this server to its MCP configuration:
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "xcart": {
      "type": "streamable-http",
      "url": "__MCP_ENDPOINT__",
      "headers": { "Authorization": "Bearer {{ mcpKey }}" }
    }
  }
}

2. If my client only supports local STDIO servers (e.g. Claude Desktop), use the mcp-remote bridge instead (requires Node.js / npx):
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "xcart": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "mcp-remote", "__MCP_ENDPOINT__", "--header", "Authorization:${XCART_MCP_AUTH}"],
      "env": { "XCART_MCP_AUTH": "Bearer {{ mcpKey }}" }
    }
  }
}

3. After updating the config, restart the client, then verify by listing the available MCP tools. This server exposes X-Cart store management: products, orders, categories, reports, and supplier category mapping (ASAP / Turn14 / SEMA Data), plus read-only resources and guided prompts.

Treat the API key as a secret — do not share or commit it.</textarea>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="settings-section">
      <h2>{{ t('Status') }}</h2>
      <table class="settings-table">
        <tr>
          <td class="setting-name">{{ t('Server Status') }}</td>
          <td class="setting-value">
            <button type="button" class="btn regular-button" id="mcp-test-connection" onclick="mcpTestConnection()">{{ t('Test Connection') }}</button>
            <span id="mcp-test-result" class="test-result" style="display:none;"></span>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>

  </div>

  {# ─────────────────────────── Tab 2: Chat ─────────────────────────── #}
  <div class="mcp-tab-panel" data-panel="chat" role="tabpanel" hidden>

    {% if not ollamaEnabled %}
      <div class="mcp-chat-disabled">
        <p>{{ t('Chat is disabled. Enable "Ollama Chat" in settings below and save to use this tab.') }}</p>
      </div>
    {% else %}
      <div class="mcp-chat-app">
        <aside class="mcp-chat-sidebar">
          <div class="mcp-chat-sidebar-head">
            <button type="button" class="btn regular-button" id="mcp-chat-new">+ {{ t('New chat') }}</button>
            <span class="mcp-chat-status" id="mcp-chat-status">{{ t('Checking Ollama…') }}</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mcp-chat-toolbar">
            <label class="mcp-chat-label">{{ t('Model') }}</label>
            <select id="mcp-chat-model" class="form-control"></select>
            <label class="mcp-chat-checkbox"><input type="checkbox" id="mcp-chat-use-tools" checked> {{ t('Use store tools') }}</label>
          </div>
          <div id="mcp-chat-list" class="mcp-chat-list"></div>
        </aside>
        <main class="mcp-chat-main">
          <div id="mcp-chat-messages" class="mcp-chat-messages"></div>
          <form id="mcp-chat-form" class="mcp-chat-input">
            <textarea id="mcp-chat-text" rows="3" placeholder="{{ t('Type a message and press Enter…') }}"></textarea>
            <button type="submit" class="btn regular-button" id="mcp-chat-send">{{ t('Send') }}</button>
          </form>
        </main>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

  </div>

</div>

<script>
(function () {
  var tabs = document.querySelectorAll('.mcp-settings .mcp-tab');
  var panels = document.querySelectorAll('.mcp-settings .mcp-tab-panel');
  tabs.forEach(function (t) {
    t.addEventListener('click', function () {
      tabs.forEach(function (x) { x.classList.remove('active'); x.setAttribute('aria-selected', 'false'); });
      panels.forEach(function (p) { p.classList.remove('active'); p.setAttribute('hidden', ''); });
      t.classList.add('active');
      t.setAttribute('aria-selected', 'true');
      var name = t.getAttribute('data-tab');
      var panel = document.querySelector('.mcp-settings .mcp-tab-panel[data-panel="' + name + '"]');
      if (panel) { panel.classList.add('active'); panel.removeAttribute('hidden'); }
      if (name === 'chat' && typeof window.__mcpChatBoot === 'function') window.__mcpChatBoot();
    });
  });
})();

(function () {
  // Fill the absolute MCP endpoint into the agent prompt using the real origin,
  // since web_dir alone may be relative.
  var ta = document.getElementById('mcp-agent-prompt');
  if (ta) {
    var base = location.origin + '{{ webDir|e('js') }}' + '/mcp';
    ta.value = ta.value.split('__MCP_ENDPOINT__').join(base);
  }
})();

function mcpCopyPrompt(btn) {
  var ta = document.getElementById('mcp-agent-prompt');
  if (!ta) return;
  var done = function () {
    var orig = btn.textContent;
    btn.textContent = '{{ t('Copied!')|e('js') }}';
    setTimeout(function () { btn.textContent = orig; }, 1500);
  };
  if (navigator.clipboard && navigator.clipboard.writeText) {
    navigator.clipboard.writeText(ta.value).then(done, function () { ta.select(); document.execCommand('copy'); done(); });
  } else {
    ta.select(); document.execCommand('copy'); done();
  }
}

function mcpTestConnection() {
  var btn = document.getElementById('mcp-test-connection');
  var result = document.getElementById('mcp-test-result');
  var apiKey = '{{ config.XC.MCP.mcp_api_key|default('')|e('js') }}';
  btn.disabled = true; btn.textContent = '{{ t('Testing...')|e('js') }}'; result.style.display = 'none';
  var headers = { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' };
  if (apiKey) headers['Authorization'] = 'Bearer ' + apiKey;
  fetch('{{ webDir|e('js') }}/mcp', { method: 'POST', headers: headers, body: JSON.stringify({
    jsonrpc: '2.0', id: 1, method: 'initialize',
    params: { protocolVersion: '2025-03-26', capabilities: {}, clientInfo: { name: 'X-Cart Admin Test', version: '1.0.0' } }
  })})
    .then(function (r) { return r.json(); })
    .then(function (data) {
      result.style.display = 'inline';
      if (data.result && data.result.serverInfo) {
        result.className = 'test-result test-success';
        result.textContent = data.result.serverInfo.name + ' v' + data.result.serverInfo.version;
      } else {
        result.className = 'test-result test-error';
        result.textContent = (data.error && data.error.message) || data.error || '{{ t('Unexpected response')|e('js') }}';
      }
    })
    .catch(function (err) {
      result.style.display = 'inline';
      result.className = 'test-result test-error';
      result.textContent = '{{ t('Connection failed')|e('js') }}: ' + err.message;
    })
    .finally(function () {
      btn.disabled = false; btn.textContent = '{{ t('Test Connection')|e('js') }}';
    });
}

{% if ollamaEnabled %}
(function () {
  var booted = false;
  var defaultModel = '{{ ollamaModel|e('js') }}';
  var urls = {
    ping:   '{{ webDir|e('js') }}/mcp-chat/ping',
    chats:  '{{ webDir|e('js') }}/mcp-chat/chats',
    chat:   '{{ webDir|e('js') }}/mcp-chat/chats/',
    send:   '{{ webDir|e('js') }}/mcp-chat/send',
  };

  var state = {
    chats: [],          // [{id, title, model, updated_at}]
    activeId: null,     // currently selected chat id (null = new)
    messages: [],       // messages for active chat
    streaming: false,
  };

  var statusEl, modelSel, useToolsEl, sidebarListEl, msgEl, textEl, sendBtn, formEl, newBtnEl;

  function escapeHtml(s) {
    return String(s == null ? '' : s).replace(/[&<>"']/g, function (c) {
      return ({'&':'&amp;','<':'&lt;','>':'&gt;','"':'&quot;',"'":'&#39;'})[c];
    });
  }

  function setStatus(text, kind) {
    if (!statusEl) return;
    statusEl.textContent = text || '';
    statusEl.className = 'mcp-chat-status' + (kind ? ' mcp-chat-status-' + kind : '');
  }

  function renderSidebar() {
    var html = state.chats.map(function (c) {
      var cls = 'mcp-chat-item' + (c.id === state.activeId ? ' active' : '');
      return '<div class="' + cls + '" data-id="' + c.id + '">' +
               '<span class="mcp-chat-item-title">' + escapeHtml(c.title || 'Chat') + '</span>' +
               '<button class="mcp-chat-item-del" data-del="' + c.id + '" title="Delete">×</button>' +
             '</div>';
    }).join('');
    sidebarListEl.innerHTML = html ||
      '<div class="mcp-chat-empty">' + 'No chats yet. Click "+ New chat".' + '</div>';
    sidebarListEl.querySelectorAll('.mcp-chat-item').forEach(function (el) {
      el.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
        if (e.target.matches('[data-del]')) return;
        var id = +el.getAttribute('data-id');
        loadChat(id);
      });
    });
    sidebarListEl.querySelectorAll('[data-del]').forEach(function (el) {
      el.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
        e.stopPropagation();
        var id = +el.getAttribute('data-del');
        deleteChat(id);
      });
    });
  }

  function renderMessages() {
    if (!state.messages.length) {
      msgEl.innerHTML = '<div class="mcp-chat-empty">Send a message to start.</div>';
      return;
    }
    var html = state.messages.map(renderMessage).join('');
    msgEl.innerHTML = html;
    msgEl.scrollTop = msgEl.scrollHeight;
  }

  function renderMessage(m) {
    var role = m.role || 'user';
    if (role === 'tool') {
      return '<details class="mcp-msg mcp-msg-tool"><summary>tool: ' + escapeHtml(m.tool_name || '?') + '</summary>' +
             '<pre>' + escapeHtml(m.content) + '</pre></details>';
    }
    var bodyHtml = '';
    if (m.tool_calls && m.tool_calls.length) {
      bodyHtml += '<div class="mcp-tool-calls">' + m.tool_calls.map(function (tc) {
        var name = (tc.function && tc.function.name) || tc.name || '?';
        var args = (tc.function && tc.function.arguments) || tc.args || {};
        return '<div class="mcp-tool-call">→ ' + escapeHtml(name) + '(' + escapeHtml(typeof args === 'string' ? args : JSON.stringify(args)) + ')</div>';
      }).join('') + '</div>';
    }
    if (m.content) bodyHtml += '<div class="mcp-msg-content">' + escapeHtml(m.content).replace(/\n/g, '<br>') + '</div>';
    return '<div class="mcp-msg mcp-msg-' + role + '">' + bodyHtml + '</div>';
  }

  function ping() {
    return fetch(urls.ping, { credentials: 'same-origin', headers: { Accept: 'application/json' } })
      .then(function (r) { return r.json().then(function (j) { return { status: r.status, body: j }; }); });
  }

  function fetchChats() {
    return fetch(urls.chats, { credentials: 'same-origin' })
      .then(function (r) { return r.json(); })
      .then(function (j) { state.chats = j.chats || []; renderSidebar(); });
  }

  function loadChat(id) {
    state.activeId = id;
    state.messages = [];
    renderSidebar();
    renderMessages();
    return fetch(urls.chat + id, { credentials: 'same-origin' })
      .then(function (r) { return r.json(); })
      .then(function (j) {
        if (j && j.chat) { state.messages = j.chat.messages || []; renderMessages(); }
      });
  }

  function deleteChat(id) {
    fetch(urls.chat + id, { method: 'DELETE', credentials: 'same-origin' })
      .then(function () {
        if (state.activeId === id) { state.activeId = null; state.messages = []; renderMessages(); }
        fetchChats();
      });
  }

  function newChat() {
    state.activeId = null;
    state.messages = [];
    renderSidebar();
    renderMessages();
    textEl.focus();
  }

  function sendMessage() {
    var text = textEl.value.trim();
    if (!text || state.streaming) return;
    textEl.value = '';

    state.streaming = true;
    sendBtn.disabled = true;

    state.messages.push({ role: 'user', content: text });
    // Track which assistant bubble we're currently writing into. Reassigned on each tool round-trip.
    var live = { role: 'assistant', content: '', tool_calls: [] };
    state.messages.push(live);
    renderMessages();

    var body = {
      text:      text,
      chat_id:   state.activeId || 0,
      model:     modelSel.value || defaultModel,
      use_tools: !!useToolsEl.checked,
    };

    fetch(urls.send, {
      method: 'POST',
      credentials: 'same-origin',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', Accept: 'text/event-stream' },
      body: JSON.stringify(body),
    })
      .then(function (resp) {
        if (!resp.ok) throw new Error('HTTP ' + resp.status);
        return consumeSse(resp.body, function (ev) {
          if (!ev || !ev.type) return;
          if (ev.type === 'meta' && ev.chat_id) {
            state.activeId = ev.chat_id;
          } else if (ev.type === 'delta') {
            live.content += ev.content || '';
            renderMessages();
          } else if (ev.type === 'tool_call') {
            live.tool_calls.push({ name: ev.name, args: ev.args, id: ev.id });
            renderMessages();
          } else if (ev.type === 'tool_result') {
            state.messages.push({ role: 'tool', tool_name: ev.name, content: ev.content });
            // Open a fresh assistant bubble for the model's next turn.
            live = { role: 'assistant', content: '', tool_calls: [] };
            state.messages.push(live);
            renderMessages();
          } else if (ev.type === 'error') {
            live.content += '\n\n[error: ' + (ev.error || 'unknown') + ']';
            renderMessages();
          }
        });
      })
      .then(function () {
        // Drop trailing empty assistant bubble (happens if the agent loop ends with a tool_result
        // but no follow-up content — rare with gemma but possible if max iterations was hit).
        var last = state.messages[state.messages.length - 1];
        if (last && last.role === 'assistant' && !last.content && (!last.tool_calls || !last.tool_calls.length)) {
          state.messages.pop();
          renderMessages();
        }
        state.streaming = false;
        sendBtn.disabled = false;
        fetchChats(); // refresh sidebar titles/timestamps
      })
      .catch(function (err) {
        live.content += '\n\n[error: ' + err.message + ']';
        renderMessages();
        state.streaming = false;
        sendBtn.disabled = false;
      });
  }

  // Async generator-style consumer of SSE; calls onEvent(parsed) per event.
  function consumeSse(stream, onEvent) {
    var reader = stream.getReader();
    var decoder = new TextDecoder('utf-8');
    var buffer = '';
    return reader.read().then(function loop(res) {
      if (res.done) return;
      buffer += decoder.decode(res.value, { stream: true });
      var parts = buffer.split('\n\n');
      buffer = parts.pop();
      parts.forEach(function (p) {
        p.split('\n').forEach(function (line) {
          if (line.indexOf('data: ') !== 0) return;
          var data = line.slice(6);
          try { onEvent(JSON.parse(data)); } catch (e) { /* ignore */ }
        });
      });
      return reader.read().then(loop);
    });
  }

  function boot() {
    if (booted) return;
    booted = true;
    statusEl     = document.getElementById('mcp-chat-status');
    modelSel     = document.getElementById('mcp-chat-model');
    useToolsEl   = document.getElementById('mcp-chat-use-tools');
    sidebarListEl= document.getElementById('mcp-chat-list');
    msgEl        = document.getElementById('mcp-chat-messages');
    textEl       = document.getElementById('mcp-chat-text');
    sendBtn      = document.getElementById('mcp-chat-send');
    formEl       = document.getElementById('mcp-chat-form');
    newBtnEl     = document.getElementById('mcp-chat-new');
    if (!msgEl) return;

    formEl.addEventListener('submit', function (e) { e.preventDefault(); sendMessage(); });
    textEl.addEventListener('keydown', function (e) {
      if (e.key === 'Enter' && !e.shiftKey) { e.preventDefault(); sendMessage(); }
    });
    newBtnEl.addEventListener('click', newChat);

    setStatus('Checking Ollama…');
    ping()
      .then(function (res) {
        if (!res.body || !res.body.ok) {
          setStatus((res.body && res.body.error) || ('HTTP ' + res.status), 'err');
          return;
        }
        var models = (res.body.models && res.body.models.length) ? res.body.models : [defaultModel];
        modelSel.innerHTML = models.map(function (n) {
          return '<option value="' + escapeHtml(n) + '"' + (n === (res.body.defaultModel || defaultModel) ? ' selected' : '') + '>' + escapeHtml(n) + '</option>';
        }).join('');
        setStatus('Connected to ' + res.body.baseUrl + ' • ' + (res.body.toolCount || 0) + ' tools', 'ok');
        return fetchChats().then(renderMessages);
      })
      .catch(function (err) {
        setStatus(String(err.message || err), 'err');
      });
  }

  window.__mcpChatBoot = boot;
})();
{% endif %}
</script>

<style>
.mcp-settings .mcp-tabs {
  display: flex; gap: 4px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #d9d9d9;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}
.mcp-settings .mcp-tab {
  background: transparent; border: 1px solid transparent; border-bottom: none;
  padding: 8px 16px; font-size: 14px; cursor: pointer; color: #555;
  border-radius: 4px 4px 0 0; margin-bottom: -1px;
}
.mcp-settings .mcp-tab:hover { background: #f4f4f4; color: #222; }
.mcp-settings .mcp-tab.active {
  background: #fff; border-color: #d9d9d9; color: #1b2838; font-weight: 600;
}
.mcp-settings .mcp-tab-panel { display: none; }
.mcp-settings .mcp-tab-panel.active { display: block; }

.mcp-settings .settings-section { margin-bottom: 30px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e5e5; }
.mcp-settings .settings-section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.mcp-settings .settings-section h2 { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 15px; color: #333; }
.mcp-settings .settings-table { width: 100%; }
.mcp-settings .settings-table td { padding: 8px 12px; vertical-align: top; }
.mcp-settings .settings-table .setting-name { width: 35%; font-weight: 500; }
.mcp-settings .settings-table .setting-name label { display: block; margin-bottom: 2px; }
.mcp-settings .help-text { font-size: 12px; color: #999; margin: 2px 0 0; }
.mcp-settings .connection-url { font-family: monospace; background: #f8f8f8; }
.mcp-settings .config-json { font-family: monospace; font-size: 12px; background: #f8f8f8; resize: vertical; }
.mcp-settings .api-key-display { font-family: monospace; background: #f0f0f0; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 3px; cursor: pointer; filter: blur(4px); transition: filter 0.2s; user-select: all; }
.mcp-settings .api-key-display.revealed { filter: none; }
.mcp-settings .test-result { font-size: 13px; vertical-align: middle; }
.mcp-settings .test-success { color: #5cb85c; font-weight: 600; }
.mcp-settings .test-error { color: #d9534f; }

.mcp-settings .mcp-chat-disabled {
  padding: 20px; background: #fff8e1; border: 1px solid #ffe0a0; border-radius: 6px; color: #6a4a00;
}
.mcp-settings .mcp-chat-app {
  display: flex; gap: 12px; height: 600px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; border-radius: 6px; overflow: hidden;
}
.mcp-settings .mcp-chat-sidebar {
  width: 260px; flex: 0 0 auto; border-right: 1px solid #e5e5e5; background: #f7f8fa;
  display: flex; flex-direction: column;
}
.mcp-settings .mcp-chat-sidebar-head {
  padding: 8px; display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center; border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
}
.mcp-settings .mcp-chat-status { font-size: 11px; color: #888; flex: 1; text-align: right; }
.mcp-settings .mcp-chat-status-ok { color: #2d8c3c; }
.mcp-settings .mcp-chat-status-err { color: #b00; }
.mcp-settings .mcp-chat-toolbar {
  padding: 8px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
}
.mcp-settings .mcp-chat-toolbar .form-control { width: 100%; font-size: 12px; padding: 4px 6px; }
.mcp-settings .mcp-chat-label { font-size: 11px; color: #555; }
.mcp-settings .mcp-chat-checkbox { font-size: 12px; color: #444; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 4px; }
.mcp-settings .mcp-chat-list { flex: 1; overflow-y: auto; }
.mcp-settings .mcp-chat-empty { padding: 16px; font-size: 12px; color: #888; text-align: center; }
.mcp-settings .mcp-chat-item {
  display: flex; align-items: center; padding: 8px 10px; font-size: 12px; cursor: pointer;
